<main id="main">
    <h1>Searching for items and storage locations</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Pay attention to the requirements</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page requires that you have installed the plentyWarehouse app on an appropriate device. Note the hardware requirements described on the <a href="/en/welcome/quick-start/quick-start-system-requirements#450">System requirements</a> page of the manual. In addition, make sure that you are logged into the plentyWarehouse app and that you have carried out <a href="/en/stock-management/installation-and-initial-setup">all necessary steps for initial setup</a>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Current state of the plentyWarehouse app</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>At the moment, plentyWarehouse is available as part of an open beta phase. This means that the app is adjusted regularly due to improvements and bug fixes. During this phase, you are welcome to ask your questions and share feedback in the <a href="https://forum.plentymarkets.com/c/app-pos/plentywarehouse/579" target="_blank" rel="noopener">forum</a> &nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentyWarehouse makes it easy for you to keep an eye on the items, stock and storage locations of your plentymarkets system at any time.
The <strong><a href="#100">Item search</a></strong> and <strong><a href="#400">Inspect storage location</a></strong> functions are available for this purpose. This manual page offers you information on their scope and on how to use them.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Item search</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do you want to look for items, display stock or view detailed information on items and variations while on the go or directly at your warehouse? The item search lets you do just that. <a href="#200">First, carry out a few settings</a> to determine what the search results should look like. These settings will go into effect when you use plentyWarehouse to <a href="#300">search for items</a> later.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="200">1.1. Carrying out settings for the item search</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>With the help of a few basic settings, you can customise the item search in plentyWarehouse so that it fits your needs and workflows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For example, you can determine how many search results are displayed at once or which search fields should be available in which order.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Carrying out settings for the item search:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/stock-management/plentywarehouse/installation-and-initial-setup#300">Log into plentyWarehouse</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the menu icon (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-bars  "></i></span>) in the top left corner.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Scroll down and tap on <strong>Settings</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="material-settings"></i></span>).<br>
→ The settings menu opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <strong>Item search</strong> <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings for the item search. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#table-pw-item-search-settings">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
